  "description": "Growing protocol for *Corchorus olitorius*, tropical heat-loving annual producing mucilaginous leaves central to Palestinian, Egyptian, Lebanese, and Indian cuisines. Seeds carry cultural lineage through generations and diaspora. Requires warm temperatures (25–35°C); unsuitable for temperate climates except as warm-season annual or greenhouse crop. 50–80 days to harvestable leaf production.",
